      "text": [
        " مَنْ رَكِبَ رَاحِلَةً فَلْيُوصِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Ahmad, from Yaqoub Bin Yazeed, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from one of his men, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who rides his ride (to go for Hajj), so let him bequeath’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "10. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Muhammad ibn Ahmad from Ya’qub ibn Yazid from ibn abu ‘Umayr from certain individuals of his people who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that if one rides a means of transportation for al-Hajj, he should make his will.” "
        ]
      }
    },
